This is the unique identifier for each transaction.
The unique identifier for the account associated with the transaction.
The date of the transaction.

value_description:
"PRIJEM" stands for credit
"VYDAJ" stands for withdrawal
llm_column_description: The type of transaction, either credit ("PRIJEM") or withdrawal ("VYDAJ").

value_description:
"VYBER KARTOU": credit card withdrawal
"VKLAD": credit in cash
"PREVOD Z UCTU" :collection from another bank
"VYBER": withdrawal in cash
"PREVOD NA UCET": remittance to another bank
llm_column_description: Mode of transaction. Possible values include "VYBER KARTOU" (credit card withdrawal), "VKLAD" (credit in cash), "PREVOD Z UCTU" (collection from another bank), "VYBER" (withdrawal in cash), and "PREVOD NA UCET" (remittance to another bank).
The amount of money involved in the transaction.
The balance after transaction.

value_description:
"POJISTNE": stands for insurrance payment
"SLUZBY": stands for payment for statement
"UROK": stands for interest credited
"SANKC. UROK": sanction interest if negative balance
"SIPO": stands for household
"DUCHOD": stands for old-age pension
"UVER": stands for loan payment
llm_column_description: Characterization of the transaction.

value_description: each bank has unique two-letter code
llm_column_description: The bank of the partner. Each bank has a unique two-letter code.
The account number associated with the transaction.
This is the unique identifier for each account.
The identifier for the district where the account is located.

value_description:
"POPLATEK MESICNE" stands for monthly issuance
"POPLATEK TYDNE" stands for weekly issuance
"POPLATEK PO OBRATU" stands for issuance after transaction
llm_column_description: The frequency of account issuance. "POPLATEK MESICNE" stands for monthly issuance, "POPLATEK TYDNE" stands for weekly issuance, and "POPLATEK PO OBRATU" stands for issuance after transaction.

column_description: the creation date of the account
